### v.0.2.0

* Fixed `flyd/module/scanmerge`
* Removed dependent stream syntax `flyd.stream([streams], combinFn)` in favor of a dedicated combine

```
var add = (a, b) => a + b;
var addCombine = flyd.combine(add);
var b = flyd.stream(0);
var a = flyd.stream(0);
var aPlusB = addCombine([a, b]);
```

The full signature is:
```
flyd.combine((depA, depB, ..., depN, self, changed) => *, [depA, depB, ..., depN]);
```

Where `self` is the combined stream and `changed` is an array of streams that have changed (subset of `depA, depB, ...`.

If the combine function will update the stream if it returns anything but `undefined`, to set the value to undefined use `self(undefined);` to update.
